The paper focuses on visual reasoning, which involves both computer vision and natural language processing. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) and cs.CL (Computation and Language) are the most likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper proposes a novel end-to-end model for visual reasoning, which involves deep learning techniques and requires intensive text-vision interactions. This suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely sub-categories. Finally, the paper mentions the use of robotics in the experiments, indicating that cs.RO (Robotics) could also be a relevant sub-category.
